node.text:
Explorer/Activist Johan Ernst Nilson. Nilson has climbed the Seven Summits (and many other peaks), visited 178 countries and some of the most remote places on Earth, and he is in the Guinness Book of World Records for his Three Poles Challenge Expedition. His travels and experiences have allowed him to see climate change and its consequences first hand, and now Nilson is an activist for change, leading people on expeditions, giving talks, and making films about the environment.

The Astronomia Everest project started with renowned Swedish explorer and environmental activist @johanernst taking an Astronomia Tourbillon with him on an expedition to the Himalayas.
"I wore the regular Astronomia Tourbillon on my last climb to the Himalayas, where I went up to 6,200 meters (almost 20,000 feet), in -30 C degree, extreme conditions," Nilson says. "You would think that such a complicated watch would be delicate and fragile, but it isn't, and it performed perfectly in all conditions. I used it climbing up ice walls, with my ice ax, banging it against rock and ice and it held up extremely well.”

Push the right-hand crown of the incredible BUGATTI Chiron Tourbillon and the engine comes to life – the crankshaft turns and the 16 pistons pump up and down, just like BUGATTI’S iconic W16 engine. Two “turbochargers” on the side of the engine block spin while the engine runs, adding to the visual impact.
Incredible to see and unbelievably complicated to realize (the movement is comprised of 578 components), the BUGATTI Chiron Tourbillon timepiece seamlessly marries engines and watches – something no other watchmaker has done before.

The Astronomia Everest project started with renowned Swedish explorer and environmental activist @johanernst taking an Astronomia Tourbillon with him on an expedition to the Himalayas.
"I wore the regular Astronomia Tourbillon on my last climb to the Himalayas, where I went up to 6,200 meters (almost 20,000 feet), in -30 C degree, extreme conditions," Nilson says. "You would think that such a complicated watch would be delicate and fragile, but it isn't, and it performed perfectly in all conditions. I used it climbing up ice walls, with my ice ax, banging it against rock and ice and it held up extremely well.”

Explorer/Activist Johan Ernst Nilson. Nilson has climbed the Seven Summits (and many other peaks), visited 178 countries and some of the most remote places on Earth, and he is in the Guinness Book of World Records for his Three Poles Challenge Expedition. His travels and experiences have allowed him to see climate change and its consequences first hand, and now Nilson is an activist for change, leading people on expeditions, giving talks, and making films about the environment.

An Incredible Icon. Now with the face of Marlon Brando, the Opera Godfather Minute Repeater uses two hammers to strike exposed circular gongs to sound out the hours, the quarters of hours, and the minutes. In the Opera Godfather Minute Repeater, the gongs circle above the dial, visible through the large sapphire crystal and rose gold case. This voluminous case enhances the clarity, tone, and richness of the sound of the gongs.

In the world of watchmaking, the presence of a tourbillon in a watch’s movement places the piece among the elite. @JacobandCo’s Twin Turbo Furious 300+ sets itself apart from this rarified group, incorporating two accelerated triple axis tourbillons into its striking design. The tourbillons work to compensate for the effects of gravity on the precision of the movement.⠀ ⠀
⠀
Even the case of the Twin Turbo Furious Bugatti 300+ is super complicated – made of forged carbon, with a titanium core to ensure water resistance - the case alone is comprised of 88 parts. The grand complication movement is made up of 832 individual parts – incredible to consider that many parts coming together, and amazing to see in action.⠀

node.text: The skeletonized movement with its vertically aligned barrel and balance wheel are viewed with exceptional clarity on the front and back of the Epic X Khabib timepiece. A bright green chapter ring made of Neoralithe, a revolutionary and tough man-made material made from resin. The watch was designed with @khabib_nurmagomedov to include many of his UFC accomplishments. His 29 - 0 record appears on the bridge of the skeletonized dial. It also appears on the sapphire crystal caseback with his signature and his iconic Papakha. #jacobandco #jacobandcowatches #khabibnurmagomedov

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by JACOB & CO. in Jacob & Co. with @jacobandco, and @khabib_nurmagomedov. May be an image of 1 person, standing and wrist watch.

node.text: UFC champion, @khabib_nurmagomedov, retired from the Octagon with a perfect 29-0 and accomplished this exceptional feat with humility, class, and style. This led Jacob Arabo, founder of Jacob & Co., to partner with Khabib to create a series of limited-edition watches. The Epic X Khabib collection has features related to Khabib’s exceptional UFC career. His 29-0 record, his nickname “The Eagle,” and his iconic Papakha, all appear on the versatile sports watch. #jacobandco #jacobandcowatches #khabibnurmagomedov

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by JACOB & CO. on September 11, 2021 tagging @jacobandco, and @khabib_nurmagomedov. May be an image of wrist watch.

node.text: It’s appropriate that a watch named after UFC champion, @khabib_nurmagomedov, would have case made of one of the strongest materials on earth. The Epic X Khabib has a black DLC grade 5 titanium case. Grade 5 titanium is considered the strongest grade of titanium, one of the strongest metals on earth. DLC stands for Diamond-Like Carbon, a thin black coating with the strength of diamond. This material strength represents the toughness of Khabib who retired from the UFC with the winningest record of all time. #jacobandco #jacobandcowatches #khabibnurmagomedov

node.text: 💎New Timepiece 💎 The Twin Turbo Furious Bugatti Sapphire Crystal timepiece is dedicated to the high-performance car manufacturer. It features a “Bugatti Blue” Neoralithe chapter ring. The color honors Bugatti’s history and French heritage. It also has the company’s logo on the front of the sapphire crystal case. It is the first watch in the history of haute horlogerie to place a decimal minute repeater inside a fully sapphire crystal case, which took approximately 15 months to design and produce, providing a fitful tribute to an iconic and historic car company. #jacobandco #jacobandcowatches #hautehorlogerie #FirstInHistory #bugatti

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by JACOB & CO. in Jacob & Co. with @jacobandco. May be an image of text that says 'JACOB &CO GENEVE UNVEILS THE FIRST MINUTE REPEATER IN A SAPPHIRE CRYSTAL CASE'.

node.text: 💎 Introducing 💎 A watch case made completely out of sapphire crystal is one of the top achievements in high watchmaking. Crafting the sapphire crystal case for the Twin Turbo Furious provided a myriad of challenges because of its complex shape and uneven surfaces. The design took about nine months and manufacturing the watch took approximately another six months. Every angle was hand polished to full transparency, allowing an unobstructed view of the 832 components of the manual winding JCFM05 caliber. #jacobandco #jacobandcowatches #hautehorlogerie #FirstInHistory

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by JACOB & CO. on September 10, 2021 tagging @jacobandco. May be an image of wrist watch and text that says 'JACO'.

node.text: 💎New Launch 💎 The Twin Turbo Furious Sapphire Crystal is the first watch in history to incorporate a minute repeater inside a sapphire crystal case. The watch comes in two models differentiated by a Neoralithe chapter ring that surrounds the dial of each watch: one in red and the other in green. The sapphire crystal case provides a full view of the complex machinery of the Twin Turbo Furious. This includes all the complications of this high-performance watch inspired by the speed and beauty of hypercars. #jacobandco #jacobandcowatches #hautehorlogerie #FirstInHistory

node.text: The color palette of Mystery Tourbillon Rainbow was created through computer-aided design prior to sourcing the stones. It took more than a year to source and cut each of the 574 stones to coincide with the predetermined row of color. #jacobandco #jacobandcowatches #hautehorlogerie

node.text: The Mystery Tourbillon Rainbow revolutionizes the approximate 200-year-old tradition of mystery dials where hour and minute hands appear to float on the dial. In this case the hours and minutes are represented by two diamonds in a sea of multicolored sapphires. In the center are two triple-axis tourbillons back-to-back driven by the manual winding JCAM32 caliber. It provides an artful work of traditional mechanical watchmaking that matches the gem-set beauty of 45 carats of multicolored sapphires. #jacobandco #jacobandcowatches #hautehorlogerie

node.text: Mystery, intrigue, and illusion are all wrapped up in one mind-boggling, ever-changing timepiece. The Mystery Tourbillon Rainbow is the only watch in the world that transforms the entire face of the dial into a completely new gemstone artwork every minute of the day. The triple rainbow sapphire rings become seamlessly aligned at the 12 o'clock position while every other moment the watch face evolves in a perpetual multi-colored metamorphosis. #jacobandco #jacobandcowatches #hautehorlogerie

node.text: From the brilliance of the 103 diamonds that adorn the crown at 12 o'clock and the bezel of the 42.5mm 18K rose gold case, to the captivating intricacy of its open-work skeleton movement, the Brilliant Pendant Watch is a fusion of haute horlogerie and exceptional craftsmanship and artistry. An 18K rose gold chain provides the perfect coda for this work of timeless adornment. #jacobandco #jacobandcowatches #hautehorology
